WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.290
Previously on "Kevin
(Probably) Saves the World"...

00:04.290 --> 00:05.620
I'm a messenger from God.
Oh, good.

00:05.620 --> 00:06.750
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

00:06.750 --> 00:08.250
The only job you have in life

00:08.250 --> 00:09.380
is to build up
your spiritual powers

00:09.380 --> 00:12.250
through acts of kindness
and selflessness.

00:12.250 --> 00:13.380
God is gonna show you

00:13.380 --> 00:15.460
how to find
the other righteous.

00:15.460 --> 00:16.500
Oh.

00:16.500 --> 00:18.000
We're not gonna
do this again, right?

00:18.000 --> 00:20.670
I'm really glad that you're not
just passing through.

00:20.670 --> 00:23.580
Tyler: I met the most
amazing woman.

00:23.580 --> 00:25.120
I met an angel, Kev.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.790
And I don't know
what to do.

00:26.790 --> 00:28.880
When are you gonna
ask Amy out?

00:28.880 --> 00:30.330
We're just...friends.

00:30.330 --> 00:31.790
There is so much more there.

00:31.790 --> 00:32.880
Dave:
She's saying you'll find

00:32.880 --> 00:34.170
a whole new generation
of the righteous.

00:34.170 --> 00:35.580
I think there aren't anymore.

00:35.580 --> 00:37.750
I convinced
35 celestial beings

00:37.750 --> 00:39.250
to give up paradise!

00:39.250 --> 00:41.250
I know where we'll find
the first righteous!

00:41.250 --> 00:42.580
Laos.

00:45.620 --> 00:49.290
I am so glad you came back.

00:49.290 --> 00:55.080
And before anyone apologizes,
let me just say...

00:55.080 --> 00:58.330
I understand why you strayed.

00:58.330 --> 01:01.750
I know some of you
have been deceived.

01:01.750 --> 01:07.830
You'd been led to believe that
our -- that our path was false.

01:07.830 --> 01:11.250
It's a time of confusion,
darkness.

01:11.250 --> 01:13.960
But now light
has banished the shadows

01:13.960 --> 01:16.290
and illuminated the truth.

01:16.290 --> 01:21.790
Friends, meet the righteous
soul who will save the world.

01:21.790 --> 01:23.580
[ Snoring ]

01:23.580 --> 01:24.790
Probably.

01:24.790 --> 01:26.040
He looks --

01:26.040 --> 01:28.330
Weak, vapid,
grotesque, even?

01:28.330 --> 01:29.580
Yes.

01:29.580 --> 01:33.250
But when this man is awake,
he is a machine.

01:33.250 --> 01:34.670
He is at one
with the universe,

01:34.670 --> 01:37.380
a divining rod
for righteous souls,

01:37.380 --> 01:39.710
waiting to be anointed.

01:39.710 --> 01:42.040
I was gonna say he looks
like a nice guy, but, yeah,

01:42.040 --> 01:44.000
I'm sure he's the stuff
you said, as well.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.380
You were right, Yvette.

01:46.380 --> 01:48.120
All this time,
you were right.

01:48.120 --> 01:50.670
About the new righteous,
about our mission --

01:50.670 --> 01:52.080
About everything!

01:52.080 --> 01:55.460
[ Laughs ]
Yes, I really was!

01:55.460 --> 01:57.830
Yes, Wayne.

01:57.830 --> 01:58.920
May we touch him?

01:58.920 --> 02:01.880
[ Snoring ]

02:01.880 --> 02:04.080
Oh, well,
what could it hurt?

02:04.080 --> 02:06.290
Get in there, get in there!
See what it is!

02:06.290 --> 02:07.670
[ Laughs ]

02:07.670 --> 02:09.540
-[ Groans ]
-Yeah.

02:11.460 --> 02:13.330
I love you, too, Nanna.

02:13.330 --> 02:14.170
[ Chuckles ]

02:14.170 --> 02:15.420
[ Snorts ]

02:15.420 --> 02:16.540
[ Spits ]

02:16.540 --> 02:17.960
[ Snorts ]

02:20.000 --> 02:22.580
Congratulations, Kevin.

02:22.580 --> 02:24.500
You're a legend.

02:30.420 --> 02:31.830
Kevin: Reese,
you're gonna be late!

02:31.830 --> 02:33.330
Reese:
Two minutes!

02:33.330 --> 02:35.290
Good morning!

02:35.290 --> 02:37.750
Um, my wake-up call
was a bunch of strangers

02:37.750 --> 02:40.790
sticking their fingers
in my mouth, so bad morning.

02:40.790 --> 02:42.580
I apologize
for my colleagues.

02:42.580 --> 02:44.460
They're just --
They're just excited.

02:44.460 --> 02:46.000
Our success has
really energized them.

02:46.000 --> 02:48.460
But no worries.
They're gone now.

02:48.460 --> 02:51.790
Good.
Reese, we got to go!

02:51.790 --> 02:53.040
Feels good, doesn't it?

02:53.040 --> 02:54.380
Hmm?
To have a clear path,

02:54.380 --> 02:57.040
to understand what
we're working towards.

02:57.040 --> 02:58.620
As long as we stay focused,

02:58.620 --> 03:01.580
I think our job
is just gonna get easier.

03:01.580 --> 03:06.460
Well, right now, my focus
is getting my niece to school.

03:06.460 --> 03:07.960
Reese!

03:07.960 --> 03:09.790
Come on!

03:09.790 --> 03:10.960
Okay.

03:10.960 --> 03:12.620
Gosh.

03:12.620 --> 03:15.330
[ Thudding ]

03:15.330 --> 03:17.000
Are you kidding me?

03:20.380 --> 03:22.120
This isn't my key.

03:22.120 --> 03:24.620
[ Gasps ]
What does it unlock?

03:24.620 --> 03:26.540
Stay focused.

03:26.540 --> 03:28.500
You know what to do.

03:28.500 --> 03:30.830
[ Sighs ]

03:30.830 --> 03:37.500
♪♪

03:37.500 --> 03:39.540
Doing your homework
on the way to school.

03:39.540 --> 03:40.750
Classic move.

03:40.750 --> 03:42.040
Shut up.
I'm almost done.

03:42.040 --> 03:44.670
14, 27, 9, 54...

03:44.670 --> 03:45.960
Shut up, please!

03:45.960 --> 03:48.880
-Morning, you two.
-Good morning, Ms. Allen.

03:48.880 --> 03:50.880
Done!
I hate you.

03:50.880 --> 03:52.380
Oh, good.
I hate you, too.

03:52.380 --> 03:54.710
Um, you know, I'm actually
glad that I ran into you,

03:54.710 --> 03:58.170
because I have
something for you.

03:58.170 --> 04:00.670
It's silly, and, you know,
I don't e-- I don't even know

04:00.670 --> 04:03.580
if you remember,
but, um...

04:03.580 --> 04:05.580
Oh, my God.

04:05.580 --> 04:06.460
Is this today?

04:06.460 --> 04:07.460
Yeah.

04:07.460 --> 04:08.710
[ Laughs ]
Wow!

04:08.710 --> 04:10.670
What's today?

04:10.670 --> 04:12.500
It's National Bird Day.

04:12.500 --> 04:13.830
Okay.

04:13.830 --> 04:15.920
When your uncle and I
were in high school,

04:15.920 --> 04:18.210
we used to celebrate
National Bird Day

04:18.210 --> 04:21.290
as a way to combat
post-holiday ennui.

04:21.290 --> 04:23.170
Oh, my God.
That's so crazy.

04:23.170 --> 04:24.290
Where did this come from?

04:24.290 --> 04:27.170
You remembered?

04:27.170 --> 04:28.120
Aww.

04:28.120 --> 04:30.580
You guys are so weird.

04:31.750 --> 04:33.170
Girl: I know, right?

04:33.170 --> 04:35.380
Hey, Reese!

04:35.380 --> 04:38.210
Reese is getting tight
with the drama kids.

04:39.460 --> 04:40.920
I'm glad she's finding
her place again.

04:40.920 --> 04:42.710
Hmm.
I think having you here

04:42.710 --> 04:46.250
has been a really -- a really
positive influence on her.

04:49.250 --> 04:51.040
I should, um...

04:51.040 --> 04:52.290
Go?
Yeah.

04:52.290 --> 04:53.380
All right.

04:53.380 --> 04:54.670
Happy National Bird Day.
Happy National --

04:54.670 --> 04:55.710
Oh.
Bye.

04:55.710 --> 04:57.250
[ Both laugh ]

04:59.620 --> 05:01.420
[ Engine starts ]

05:01.420 --> 05:03.580
[ Lionel Richie's "Hello"
plays on radio ]
Oh!

05:03.580 --> 05:04.920
Whoo!

05:04.920 --> 05:05.880
I love this song.

05:05.880 --> 05:07.290
Uh, no.

05:07.290 --> 05:09.420
♪ I wonder where you are ♪

05:09.420 --> 05:11.420
♪ How much I care ♪

05:11.420 --> 05:12.460
Will you stop doing that?

05:12.460 --> 05:13.670
It's not me.

05:13.670 --> 05:14.540
Fine.
[ Music stops ]

05:14.540 --> 05:15.580
No music today.

05:15.580 --> 05:17.960
[ Music starts ]

05:17.960 --> 05:19.880
I think the Universe
likes this song, too.

05:19.880 --> 05:21.250
[ Sighs ]

05:21.250 --> 05:23.960
♪ Tell me how
to win your heart ♪

05:23.960 --> 05:26.540
♪ For I haven't got ♪

05:26.540 --> 05:29.170
Morning. We have a new
student starting today.

05:29.170 --> 05:31.580
This is Jessica,
from Seattle.

05:31.580 --> 05:33.710
Can you all give her
a warm La Salle welcome?

05:33.710 --> 05:37.080
[ Light applause ]

05:37.080 --> 05:39.580
That was truly, truly inspiring.

05:39.580 --> 05:42.830
Now, Jessica's student buddy
is out sick today.

05:42.830 --> 05:44.750
Would anyone like to volunteer

05:44.750 --> 05:47.290
to act as Jessica's
substitute buddy?

05:49.830 --> 05:51.960
Guys, come on.
You're bumming me out.

05:51.960 --> 05:54.880
It's cool.
Um, I'll figure it out.

05:54.880 --> 05:56.580
[ Chuckles nervously ]

05:56.580 --> 06:06.210
♪♪

06:06.210 --> 06:09.290
Kevin: I have been dreaming of
these since we were in Laos.

06:09.290 --> 06:12.170
Well, you deserve
to treat yourself,

06:12.170 --> 06:15.540
because we have
been killin' it!

06:15.540 --> 06:17.080
[ Both laugh ]

06:17.080 --> 06:19.040
Ooh, sweet cinder block.

06:19.040 --> 06:20.750
Oh. Thanks.

06:20.750 --> 06:23.250
So, I found this
Canadian website

06:23.250 --> 06:25.250
that posts listings
for missed connections.

06:25.250 --> 06:26.960
Uh-huh.
I'm writing one.

06:26.960 --> 06:29.960
I'm calling it
"Laos and Found."

06:29.960 --> 06:30.960
That's good, right?

06:30.960 --> 06:31.710
That is great.

06:31.710 --> 06:33.040
[ Both laugh ]

06:33.040 --> 06:34.170
Mind if I run
something by you?

06:34.170 --> 06:36.790
Yeah, go for it.

06:36.790 --> 06:38.500
"I was a traveler in Laos,

06:38.500 --> 06:41.540
hitting the hotel bar
in search of a scorpion bowl.

06:41.540 --> 06:44.420
You were a beautiful lady
with soulful eyes

06:44.420 --> 06:47.880
and hands as soft as tissues
with lotion in them."

06:47.880 --> 06:51.540
You know, Canada is,
uh -- it's pretty big.

06:51.540 --> 06:53.920
There's a chance that
she may never see it.

06:53.920 --> 06:55.920
Mm. Not possible.

06:55.920 --> 06:57.670
If she's feeling half
of what I'm feeling,

06:57.670 --> 07:00.040
she's probably
looking for me, too.

07:00.040 --> 07:01.540
I'm-a keep
working on this.

07:01.540 --> 07:03.880
You're the best, Kevlar.

07:09.000 --> 07:10.250
Let me feel your hands.

07:10.250 --> 07:11.750
No!

07:11.750 --> 07:13.080
It's you.

07:13.080 --> 07:14.670
Admit it.

07:14.670 --> 07:16.500
[ Sighs ]

07:16.500 --> 07:17.380
Come on.

07:17.380 --> 07:19.460
So...

07:19.460 --> 07:22.250
So, I want to have a drink
at the hotel bar...

07:22.250 --> 07:23.210
Oh, my God. Okay.
And then?

07:23.210 --> 07:24.540
And then nothing.

07:24.540 --> 07:26.120
I didn't think
he was gonna be there.

07:26.120 --> 07:28.920
I thought I could be
anonymous.

07:28.920 --> 07:30.670
Okay.

07:30.670 --> 07:34.790
So, you shared a drink,
talked a little, and then, uh...

07:34.790 --> 07:35.710
Yeah.
...and then made,

07:35.710 --> 07:37.120
sweet, sweet --

07:37.120 --> 07:39.540
Kevin, I will end you.

07:39.540 --> 07:41.420
I will end you right now.

07:41.420 --> 07:45.710
Whatever he's experiencing
is entirely in his head.

07:45.710 --> 07:47.920
Well, I don't know
about that.

07:47.920 --> 07:51.040
I mean, I think it seems like
the real deal for him.

07:54.580 --> 07:57.830
[ Gasps ]

07:57.830 --> 07:59.420
Okay. Now that's just mean.

08:01.170 --> 08:03.580
[ Doorbell rings ]

08:03.580 --> 08:05.880
♪♪

08:05.880 --> 08:07.580
I have a delivery
for Kevin Finn?

08:07.580 --> 08:08.500
Oh, that's me.

08:08.500 --> 08:10.210
Here you go.

08:11.670 --> 08:13.920
Where's the, uh --
the package?

08:13.920 --> 08:15.790
Right here.

08:15.790 --> 08:17.580
-That's for me?
-Yeah.

08:17.580 --> 08:20.420
-Who sent it?
-Uh...

08:20.420 --> 08:22.750
Just says here
it's from New York City.

08:22.750 --> 08:24.540
You got a key, right?

08:24.540 --> 08:26.620
I...

08:27.540 --> 08:29.540
Oh!
Actually, I do.

08:32.790 --> 08:34.420
Oh.

08:34.420 --> 08:36.460
It's my old stuff from New York.

08:36.460 --> 08:38.380
That's so weird.

08:38.380 --> 08:40.290
Why would the Universe
send this to me?

08:40.290 --> 08:43.000
Maybe there's something
in here that'll tell us.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.120
Kevin?
Uh, what is this?

08:46.120 --> 08:48.420
It's my, uh -- my stuff
from New York.

08:48.420 --> 08:52.500
It was in storage,
and it got sent to me.

08:52.500 --> 08:54.380
Uh, would you give me
a hand moving it in?

08:54.380 --> 08:55.790
Sure can't.

08:55.790 --> 08:57.210
Why not?

08:57.210 --> 08:59.290
Because you have
terrible taste.

08:59.290 --> 09:02.380
Aim.

09:02.380 --> 09:03.580
Airplane chair?

09:03.580 --> 09:04.750
Ah.

09:04.750 --> 09:07.500
With so many
decorative rivets.

09:07.500 --> 09:09.120
Kevin, I would actually
rather sit on the floor

09:09.120 --> 09:11.750
for the rest of my life than
have that chair inside my house,

09:11.750 --> 09:13.210
so...

09:13.210 --> 09:14.960
Just, yeah, you know what?
Just get rid of it.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.790
I'm keeping
some things, though.

09:18.170 --> 09:19.830
This.

09:19.830 --> 09:22.420
My favorite lamp.

09:22.420 --> 09:24.250
And these.

09:26.290 --> 09:28.080
[ Sighs ] Oof!

09:28.080 --> 09:31.290
All right, well, you drive
a pretty hard bargain.

09:31.290 --> 09:33.210
-Hm.
-So, okay.

09:33.210 --> 09:35.000
Get rid of the lamp,
though.

09:36.710 --> 09:38.790
It's fine. We'll send
a truck to pick up the rest.

09:38.790 --> 09:40.540
Okay.

09:40.540 --> 09:43.120
Sorry.

09:46.170 --> 09:49.120
Feels good to be getting rid of
all that stuff, am I right?

09:49.120 --> 09:51.000
Totally.

09:52.790 --> 09:54.380
I always hated
these sheets.

09:54.380 --> 09:55.920
My ex loved them.

09:55.920 --> 09:57.920
Scratchy as hell.

09:57.920 --> 10:00.250
Oh. That's the worst.

10:00.250 --> 10:02.210
Yeah, all this stuff
was hers.

10:02.210 --> 10:03.580
Just getting rid of it.

10:03.580 --> 10:04.920
Starting clean.

10:04.920 --> 10:06.540
Cool.

10:06.540 --> 10:08.790
Just happy to be moving on.

10:09.380 --> 10:10.170
Charlie.

10:10.170 --> 10:11.380
Oh. Kevin.

10:11.380 --> 10:12.500
[ Both chuckle ]

10:12.500 --> 10:15.500
♪ Hello ♪

10:15.500 --> 10:17.210
♪ Is it me you're looking for? ♪

10:17.210 --> 10:18.920
Oh.

10:18.920 --> 10:20.960
Song's been following
me around all day.

10:20.960 --> 10:22.960
[ Chuckles ]
Wow.

10:22.960 --> 10:24.120
Weird.

10:24.120 --> 10:26.210
Yeah.

10:26.210 --> 10:29.080
This was -- This was
actually our song.

10:29.080 --> 10:30.460
Really?

10:30.460 --> 10:31.710
Yeah.

10:31.710 --> 10:33.380
Huh.

10:33.380 --> 10:35.670
Yeah, I haven't
heard it in a while.

10:35.670 --> 10:38.210
Mm.

10:38.210 --> 10:42.830
It's, uh, a little
upsetting, actually.

10:42.830 --> 10:45.210
Do you want me to see if
I can turn it off, or...?

10:45.210 --> 10:46.540
Yeah. That might be good.

10:46.540 --> 10:47.790
Okay.

10:47.790 --> 10:49.960
Uh, easy...

10:49.960 --> 10:51.670
Easy.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.750
♪ I long to see
the sunlight in your hair ♪

10:56.750 --> 10:58.580
Uh, hang on.

10:58.580 --> 11:00.540
Uh, I'll find it.
Yeah, uh...

11:00.540 --> 11:03.380
Oh! Got it.
Here it is.

11:03.380 --> 11:05.880
♪ And tell you time
and time again ♪

11:05.880 --> 11:08.460
♪ How much I care ♪

11:08.460 --> 11:12.250
Seriously, could you just...
get it off?

11:12.250 --> 11:13.710
Yeah, I'm just,
uh, trying.

11:13.710 --> 11:15.170
Just a sec.

11:16.750 --> 11:18.620
♪ Hello ♪

11:18.620 --> 11:19.960
[ Chuckles nervously ]

11:19.960 --> 11:21.290
-Please...
-Uh...

11:21.290 --> 11:24.500
♪ I've just got
to let you know ♪

11:24.500 --> 11:25.920
♪ 'Cause I wonder
where you are ♪

11:25.920 --> 11:28.540
Okay.

11:28.540 --> 11:32.620
♪ And I wonder what you do ♪

11:32.620 --> 11:34.580
♪ Are you somewhere
feeling lonely? ♪

11:34.580 --> 11:36.420
-Seriously, not funny, man.
-No, I'm not trying to...

11:36.420 --> 11:40.080
♪ Or is someone loving you? ♪

11:40.080 --> 11:42.040
♪ Tell me how
to win your heart ♪

11:42.040 --> 11:44.040
Not funny.

11:44.040 --> 11:46.750
♪ For I haven't got a clue ♪

11:46.750 --> 11:48.920
-Oh, boy.
-Yeah.

11:48.920 --> 11:50.580
Uh, uh...

11:50.580 --> 11:52.000
♪ But let me start by saying ♪

11:52.000 --> 11:53.250
Found it!
There it is.

11:53.250 --> 11:54.170
-Okay.
-♪ I love you ♪

11:54.170 --> 11:55.710
Uh, yeah.

11:55.710 --> 11:58.040
Okay. Uh...

12:00.290 --> 12:01.710
[ Crashing ]

12:01.710 --> 12:02.920
It's okay.

12:02.920 --> 12:04.670
[ Groaning ] I'm okay.

12:04.670 --> 12:05.710
♪ Hello ♪

12:05.710 --> 12:06.500
[ Music stops ]

12:10.420 --> 12:11.960
Kevin: Don't be crazy.
You're not gonna die alone.

12:11.960 --> 12:13.080
You're gonna meet
someone right away.

12:13.080 --> 12:14.960
Oh. I'm gonna sit.

12:14.960 --> 12:16.790
It's not that.
It's just...

12:16.790 --> 12:18.330
I had something real.

12:18.330 --> 12:20.290
You know, we'd...

12:20.290 --> 12:22.290
cook dinner together
and read the same books.

12:22.290 --> 12:27.170
You know, plan these
long, epic road trips.

12:27.170 --> 12:29.710
I mean,
I want that again.

12:29.710 --> 12:31.040
Okay. But...

12:31.040 --> 12:32.500
Now you're getting
way ahead of yourself.

12:32.500 --> 12:34.750
I mean, you need to --
You need to meet some people

12:34.750 --> 12:35.670
before that happens.

12:35.670 --> 12:37.290
Baby steps.

12:37.290 --> 12:39.920
Just grab some friends,
go to a bar...

12:39.920 --> 12:41.170
Get out there.

12:41.170 --> 12:42.960
All my friends
are married with kids.

12:42.960 --> 12:44.380
They're in bed by 9:00.

12:44.380 --> 12:46.040
How about -- How about
I take you out tonight?

12:46.040 --> 12:47.830
[ Chuckles ]

12:47.830 --> 12:49.790
Yeah, I don't know.

12:49.790 --> 12:51.880
I've been wanting to try
that new beer garden

12:51.880 --> 12:53.380
down on Spring Street.

12:53.380 --> 12:56.750
I do like gardens,
especially beer ones.

12:56.750 --> 12:58.040
Well, there you go.
Let's --

12:58.040 --> 13:00.500
[ Ring tone plays ]
Oh.

13:00.500 --> 13:02.500
Ah. My niece forgot
her history book.

13:02.500 --> 13:05.040
Okay. Uh --
Oh, I got to run.

13:05.040 --> 13:08.330
Um, well, meet
tonight at 7:00.

13:08.330 --> 13:13.420
And, uh -- And bring your, uh --
your garden...equipment.

13:13.420 --> 13:14.920
Sorry. I gave up on
that one midway through.

13:14.920 --> 13:15.670
Spring Street?
Yeah.

13:15.670 --> 13:17.750
All right.

13:17.750 --> 13:21.120
Okay, guys, we are all going
to read chapter 9 and discuss

13:21.120 --> 13:23.670
the platform that led to
the election of Herbert Hoover.

13:23.670 --> 13:27.250
Some key terms to consider --
during the campaign,

13:27.250 --> 13:29.290
Herbert Hoover pointed
to the success of

13:29.290 --> 13:30.960
the "Own Your Own Home"
program...

13:30.960 --> 13:32.040
Reese!
...which he created

13:32.040 --> 13:33.460
while he was
the Secretary of Commerce.

13:33.460 --> 13:35.080
Hey. Could you pass
this over to Reese?

13:35.080 --> 13:36.620
But although the program was
designed to help people,

13:36.620 --> 13:38.790
it actually contributed
to the destabilization

13:38.790 --> 13:40.250
of the banking system.

13:40.250 --> 13:41.670
The program was designed
to boost the level...

13:41.670 --> 13:43.210
It's Kevin.

13:43.210 --> 13:45.170
...of home ownership
in the U.S.A....

13:45.170 --> 13:46.830
Reese.
...through new rules

13:46.830 --> 13:48.210
which allowed
the federally chartered banks

13:48.210 --> 13:49.120
to expand their
mortgage lending.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.920
How's your day
going so far?

13:50.920 --> 13:52.710
Also, relaxing regulations
for the Federal Reserve Bank...

13:52.710 --> 13:54.170
Hey, bud,
is that a henley?

13:54.170 --> 13:55.500
I used to wear those
all the time.

13:55.500 --> 13:56.920
You into baseball?
Shh!

13:56.920 --> 13:58.420
I am talking
to my new friend.

13:58.420 --> 14:01.880
Okay. What's going
on back there?

14:01.880 --> 14:04.620
Okay. Um...

14:08.710 --> 14:09.710
-Hi.
-Hey!

14:09.710 --> 14:10.880
Just teaching?

14:10.880 --> 14:11.790
Trying.

14:11.790 --> 14:13.250
Cool. [ Chuckles ]

14:13.250 --> 14:15.380
Actually,
could you come in?

14:15.380 --> 14:17.420
Uh...really?

14:17.420 --> 14:19.210
Yeah. No, I just --
I got to go check on

14:19.210 --> 14:21.420
Miss Saffert's room because
the substitute was late.

14:21.420 --> 14:24.290
Um, could you just
watch the kids for --

14:24.290 --> 14:26.670
I don't know --
a few minutes?

14:26.670 --> 14:29.170
Yeah, I'm sure I could teach
these youngsters a thing or two.

14:29.170 --> 14:30.250
Okay. That's great.

14:30.250 --> 14:32.380
Guys, keep reading
chapter 9 quietly,

14:32.380 --> 14:33.670
and I will be right back.

14:33.670 --> 14:35.500
Okay.

14:35.500 --> 14:42.210
♪♪

14:42.210 --> 14:45.620
So, what's in chapter 9, guys?

14:45.620 --> 14:48.620
Oh! You're doing
the Great Depression.

14:48.620 --> 14:52.670
Well, good news --
I know all about that.

14:52.670 --> 14:57.250
Um, watch this --
it was very depressing.

14:57.250 --> 14:59.830
But...

14:59.830 --> 15:02.880
great, because it --

15:02.880 --> 15:05.580
Well, it showed that
the banking system was flawed.

15:05.580 --> 15:09.420
And, um, I-I actually --
I was an investment banker

15:09.420 --> 15:11.710
for quite a long time, so, uh --

15:11.710 --> 15:14.330
[ chuckles ] -- believe me,
I saw things

15:14.330 --> 15:16.290
you would not believe.

15:16.290 --> 15:20.920
It is a dark and horrible

15:20.920 --> 15:24.250
but exciting world.

15:24.250 --> 15:26.330
And apparently,
they're pretty happy,

15:26.330 --> 15:29.120
but you know who
is not very happy,

15:29.120 --> 15:31.460
uh, are his wife and kids.

15:31.460 --> 15:33.380
[ Laughter ]
So, you know, little lesson --

15:33.380 --> 15:34.710
don't fake your own death.

15:34.710 --> 15:36.000
It's harder than it looks.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.250
But -- ooh! -- we had
this other client who flew

15:38.250 --> 15:41.380
to the Caymans
with $12 million -- in cash --

15:41.380 --> 15:45.790
duct-taped to his body because
he stopped trusting the banks.

15:45.790 --> 15:49.250
So, in a way,
the -- the same thinking

15:49.250 --> 15:50.420
that sparked
the Great Depression

15:50.420 --> 15:52.040
is still alive today.

15:52.040 --> 15:54.920
Did he --
Did he fly first-class?

15:54.920 --> 15:56.620
Weirdly, coach.

15:56.620 --> 15:58.420
-Oh.
-Yeah. Oh!

15:58.420 --> 16:00.210
And he had to wear
this big old adult diaper

16:00.210 --> 16:01.960
because he didn't want
to use the restroom.

16:01.960 --> 16:03.880
[ Laughter ]
Okay. I think
I got it from here.

16:03.880 --> 16:05.620
Uh, thank you,
Mr. Finn.

16:05.620 --> 16:07.290
-Hey, glad to lend a hand.
-Good job.

16:07.290 --> 16:08.620
[ School bell rings ]
Oh. All right, guys,

16:08.620 --> 16:10.420
please finish reading chapter 9.

16:10.420 --> 16:12.210
May or may not be
a pop quiz next week.

16:12.210 --> 16:13.670
I don't know.

16:15.170 --> 16:16.580
Hi. Jessica?

16:16.580 --> 16:17.380
Uh, hi.

16:17.380 --> 16:18.880
I'm Reese.

16:18.880 --> 16:21.500
If you're still interested,
I can show you around.

16:21.500 --> 16:24.120
Maybe tomorrow we can
have lunch together?

16:24.120 --> 16:25.580
Yeah.
That'd be awesome.

16:25.580 --> 16:26.330
All right.

16:26.330 --> 16:27.880
Okay.

16:30.290 --> 16:34.170
"To my lady in Laos.

16:34.170 --> 16:38.540
We danced to the finest mariachi
music in Southeast Asia,

16:38.540 --> 16:42.790
and it was...

16:42.790 --> 16:43.920
magical."

16:43.920 --> 16:45.920
Okay. Calm down.

16:45.920 --> 16:49.290
"Dancing with you
felt like..."

16:49.290 --> 16:51.080
[ Sighs ]

16:51.080 --> 16:54.380
"...the beach on a summer day."

16:54.380 --> 16:57.670
Mm. Now, that -- that --
that actually sounds nice.

16:57.670 --> 17:00.500
"I know losing someone
this special would normally

17:00.500 --> 17:04.460
crush a person -- I mean,
just rip their heart out.

17:06.580 --> 17:11.710
But I know deep down,
I'll see you again.

17:11.710 --> 17:13.710
We'll be together.

17:13.710 --> 17:18.170
And then, every day
will be like summer."

17:19.670 --> 17:22.460
[ Computer beeps ]

17:22.460 --> 17:24.830
That'll work.

17:24.830 --> 17:26.540
That'll definitely work.

17:32.620 --> 17:34.460
All right.

17:34.460 --> 17:37.500
You want a wingman,
or you want to fly solo?

17:37.500 --> 17:40.170
There's nobody here for me.
I can already tell.

17:40.170 --> 17:42.080
You don't have
to find a soul mate,

17:42.080 --> 17:45.580
just someone who you don't mind
talking to for a few minutes.

17:45.580 --> 17:47.120
Then what? A date?

17:47.120 --> 17:49.620
[ Scoffs ]
That sounds horrible.

17:49.620 --> 17:52.330
Again, I think you're putting
too much pressure on this.

17:52.330 --> 17:54.420
If you find someone
who interests you,

17:54.420 --> 17:57.120
we can -- we can
go out as a group.

17:57.120 --> 18:00.460
Okay.
I'll go meet some people.

18:00.460 --> 18:01.920
All right.

18:01.920 --> 18:03.750
[ Chuckles ]

18:03.750 --> 18:06.420
I was wrong.

18:06.420 --> 18:08.670
I think I ruined
your friend Tyler.

18:08.670 --> 18:10.040
How? Is he okay?

18:10.040 --> 18:12.710
He's fine...for now.

18:12.710 --> 18:15.880
He's so sure we're gonna
find each other.

18:15.880 --> 18:18.330
But that's
never gonna happen?

18:18.330 --> 18:21.120
I mean, even if I appear
to him again, we could --

18:21.120 --> 18:24.000
we could never be, you know,
what he wants us to be.

18:24.000 --> 18:25.670
That's -- That's just
not how it works.

18:25.670 --> 18:27.080
Oh.

18:27.080 --> 18:29.460
And I'm worried about
how Tyler's gonna take it

18:29.460 --> 18:32.420
when he realizes his
"Lady from Laos"

18:32.420 --> 18:34.920
isn't coming back.

18:34.920 --> 18:36.500
Yeah, heartache's tough,

18:36.500 --> 18:39.420
especially when you have
as big a heart as he does.

18:39.420 --> 18:43.580
He is a pure soul --
maybe the purest I've met.

18:43.580 --> 18:46.330
I mean, I never should've
allowed him to see me.

18:46.330 --> 18:47.920
It was a mistake.
That was a mistake.

18:47.920 --> 18:49.540
I mean, I don't know
what I was thinking.

18:49.540 --> 18:52.000
-Hey, Kevin.
-Hey. Oh!

18:52.000 --> 18:53.290
That was --
That was quick.

18:53.290 --> 18:54.830
Do you need
a little support?

18:54.830 --> 18:57.750
I talked to someone
that didn't make me nauseous.

18:57.750 --> 18:59.540
That's great.

18:59.540 --> 19:01.880
I hope the offer
for the group date was real,

19:01.880 --> 19:03.420
'cause I asked her out.

19:03.420 --> 19:05.580
Of course it's --
it's still good, yeah.

19:05.580 --> 19:08.290
I mean, I -- I know exactly
who I'll ask to join us.

19:08.290 --> 19:09.790
[ Chuckles ]

19:09.790 --> 19:11.960
Where's your, uh --
Where's your lucky lady?

19:11.960 --> 19:13.830
Um...

19:13.830 --> 19:16.040
The brunette right there
in the dress.

19:16.040 --> 19:18.000
Right there.

19:18.000 --> 19:19.500
Great!

19:19.500 --> 19:21.000
Oh, so great.

19:21.000 --> 19:23.500
That's just...great.

19:23.500 --> 19:24.710
[ Chuckles ]

19:24.710 --> 19:26.500
Great!

19:26.500 --> 19:28.290
Ugh.

19:33.460 --> 19:35.540
Kevin: Nope.

19:35.540 --> 19:37.620
Nope.

19:37.620 --> 19:39.250
Nope.

19:39.250 --> 19:41.330
Is that Melanie Tripp?

19:41.330 --> 19:43.080
Yep.

19:43.080 --> 19:45.670
Recently released from a short
prison stint for larceny.

19:45.670 --> 19:46.580
Ah.
Yeah.

19:46.580 --> 19:47.960
Skipping down
memory lane?

19:47.960 --> 19:49.750
Mm, kind of.

19:49.750 --> 19:52.960
Hey, is, um --
is Lori still annoying?

19:52.960 --> 19:55.040
[ Chuckles ]
She does that, "How are you?"

19:55.040 --> 19:56.790
Oh, yeah.
Yes, she is.

19:56.790 --> 19:58.500
What are you doing?
[ Sighs ]

19:58.500 --> 20:01.000
I-I-I just got to find
a plus-one for tonight.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.250
I kind of promised
someone that I'd go on

20:03.250 --> 20:04.580
a double date with them.

20:04.580 --> 20:06.460
Why don't you
ask Kristin?

20:06.460 --> 20:07.880
You guys have been
hanging out, haven't you?

20:07.880 --> 20:09.250
Yes, we have.

20:09.250 --> 20:10.330
The problem with that is,

20:10.330 --> 20:12.080
she's the other half
of the double date.

20:12.080 --> 20:13.380
Oh.

20:13.380 --> 20:14.710
Oh, indeed.

20:14.710 --> 20:16.330
You know, I always
thought you guys

20:16.330 --> 20:18.620
would get back
together someday.

20:18.620 --> 20:20.170
Really?
Yeah.

20:20.170 --> 20:22.210
I don't know.
You two just seemed to click.

20:22.210 --> 20:23.540
You balanced
each other out.

20:23.540 --> 20:25.330
Okay, okay, okay, come on.
Move over.

20:25.330 --> 20:28.460
So, you were trying
to find a terrible date

20:28.460 --> 20:31.210
to make sure that
Kristin knows

20:31.210 --> 20:32.880
that you are not
interested in them.

20:32.880 --> 20:33.920
I'll find someone.
No, no, no.

20:33.920 --> 20:35.380
You know what?

20:35.380 --> 20:38.000
I have the perfect
terrible date for you.

20:38.000 --> 20:40.670
The STEM club
hangs right over there.

20:40.670 --> 20:44.420
I've gone to school with most of
these people since kindergarten.

20:44.420 --> 20:46.210
Mostly everyone is okay.

20:46.210 --> 20:47.250
Cool.

20:47.250 --> 20:48.960
Thanks for
showing me around.

20:48.960 --> 20:51.250
I know it's kind of weird
when people are like,

20:51.250 --> 20:52.960
"Hey, be friends
with this stranger."

20:52.960 --> 20:54.290
No big deal.

20:54.290 --> 20:55.830
Where do you sit?

20:55.830 --> 20:57.920
I used to sit by myself.

20:57.920 --> 21:02.080
-Hey, Reese!
-But I've kind of gotten into

21:02.080 --> 21:04.080
theater recently, so...

21:04.080 --> 21:06.330
Nice. New posse.

21:06.330 --> 21:09.580
Uh, this is Jessica.
She's new.

21:09.580 --> 21:12.250
This is Alex, Kai,
Rory, and Zoe.

21:12.250 --> 21:13.620
-Mm-hmm.
-Reese, did you finish

21:13.620 --> 21:15.920
your history?
-Yeah, in study hall.

21:15.920 --> 21:17.920
I'm still
working on mine.

21:17.920 --> 21:19.460
Uh, did you
forget your lunch?

21:19.460 --> 21:21.460
Nope.

21:21.460 --> 21:24.120
I have to go to Miss Allen's
'cause she wants to discuss

21:24.120 --> 21:25.790
my review
of the play, so...

21:25.790 --> 21:28.290
You were a little harsh.

21:28.290 --> 21:29.960
It's why they call it
a critique, Alex.

21:29.960 --> 21:32.210
Are you done with that?

21:32.210 --> 21:33.170
Yeah.

21:33.170 --> 21:34.620
Can I finish it?

21:34.620 --> 21:38.120
Uh...sure.

21:38.120 --> 21:40.710
Thanks.

21:40.710 --> 21:43.040
I can loan you some
lunch money if you want to...

21:43.040 --> 21:44.210
Oh, it's not
about the money.

21:44.210 --> 21:45.920
I never buy lunch.

21:45.920 --> 21:49.170
I'm kind of like
an urban forager.

21:49.170 --> 21:51.040
What does that mean?

21:51.040 --> 21:52.540
I eat food before
it gets thrown out.

21:52.540 --> 21:55.540
Do you know 40% of food
in America is never eaten?

21:55.540 --> 21:57.920
Perfectly good food just
thrown away like garbage.

21:57.920 --> 21:59.540
This is really good, though.

21:59.540 --> 22:01.750
Thank you.

22:01.750 --> 22:04.120
[ Humming ]

22:04.120 --> 22:05.920
Mm. Are you
gonna finish that?

22:05.920 --> 22:08.040
No.
Thank you.

22:08.040 --> 22:11.790
♪♪

22:11.790 --> 22:14.000
Here you go.
Thank you.

22:15.420 --> 22:17.120
I'm really glad
we could get together.

22:17.120 --> 22:21.540
I've been kind of off
the dating circuit for a while.

22:21.540 --> 22:23.880
And I'm not great
at meeting people.

22:23.880 --> 22:25.500
Me neither.

22:25.500 --> 22:27.710
It's awful, isn't it?
Yeah.

22:27.710 --> 22:30.830
Dating apps and setups,
just leave everything to chance?

22:30.830 --> 22:32.380
I-I never know what I'm --

22:32.380 --> 22:34.040
Never know what I'm doing.

22:34.040 --> 22:36.380
Oh. And I asked some
friends to join us,

22:36.380 --> 22:38.500
if you're okay with that.
Yeah.

22:38.500 --> 22:42.710
You know, to take the pressure
off, keep it casual.

22:42.710 --> 22:44.710
Keepin' it casual is great.

22:44.710 --> 22:45.920
That's -- That's perfect.

22:45.920 --> 22:47.710
That's great.
[ Laughs ]

22:47.710 --> 22:49.750
Oh! There he is.
Hey, man!

22:51.540 --> 22:55.710
Oh! So, you're -- So you're
friends with Kevin?

22:55.710 --> 22:56.830
You guys
know each other?

22:56.830 --> 22:58.540
Hey.
Yeah.

22:58.540 --> 23:01.880
Yeah, we -- we -- we...went
to school together, so...

23:01.880 --> 23:03.710
Wow! This is funny,
isn't it?

23:03.710 --> 23:05.420
[ Chuckles ]

23:05.420 --> 23:06.790
Is your, uh,
date on the way?

23:06.790 --> 23:07.880
-Hey!
-Um, actually --

23:07.880 --> 23:09.380
-Hey, there! Hi!
-[ Spits ]

23:09.380 --> 23:11.040
-Hi. Amy.
-Charlie.

23:11.040 --> 23:12.830
-Nice to meet you.
-We're -- This is --

23:12.830 --> 23:13.880
We're doing this.

23:13.880 --> 23:15.250
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

23:15.250 --> 23:17.420
So, you guys ready
to double date?

23:17.420 --> 23:19.000
Well, we don't have
to keep calling it that.

23:19.000 --> 23:20.500
Uh, does anyone
want drinks?

23:25.330 --> 23:28.080
So, wait, um...you brought
your sister...as a date?

23:28.080 --> 23:29.420
[ Clears throat ]

23:29.420 --> 23:30.960
See, this is --

23:30.960 --> 23:33.290
I feel like this is one of those
crossed-wire situations.

23:33.290 --> 23:35.120
I thought, uh, that
this was more of, like,

23:35.120 --> 23:36.830
a group hang
more than a date.

23:36.830 --> 23:39.040
-Oh.
-So, yeah.

23:39.040 --> 23:40.380
I definitely thought
it was a date.

23:40.380 --> 23:42.620
Same.
Yeah, well, maybe misheard.

23:42.620 --> 23:44.960
I mean, "hang" and "date" --
they sound so much alike.

23:44.960 --> 23:47.040
-Yeah.
-No, not really.

23:47.040 --> 23:50.250
Well, "hang" "date,"
you know...

23:50.250 --> 23:52.380
"Hey, we're going on
a group hang."

23:52.380 --> 23:55.210
"Hey, uh, it's almost time
for our group hang."

23:59.380 --> 24:00.880
So, it's crazy random
that you guys all

24:00.880 --> 24:01.920
knew each other
in high school, right?

24:01.920 --> 24:03.460
-Crazy.
-Yeah.

24:03.460 --> 24:05.460
It was a little more
than that, you two.

24:05.460 --> 24:07.380
These guys were
quite the couple.

24:07.380 --> 24:09.120
[ Chuckles ]

24:09.120 --> 24:10.540
Major item.

24:10.540 --> 24:11.920
Well, ma-major item --
that's a bit much.

24:11.920 --> 24:12.920
I wouldn't have
really have said --

24:12.920 --> 24:15.540
Yeah.
Minor item.

24:15.540 --> 24:18.000
Even not -- Minor friendship,
if even an item.

24:18.000 --> 24:20.210
-Just two minors.
-Pfft!

24:20.210 --> 24:21.580
-You guys.
-Hmm?

24:21.580 --> 24:25.420
People went as you guys
for Halloween.

24:25.420 --> 24:27.920
Yeah. They even had a very cute
couple nickname.

24:27.920 --> 24:30.000
-Stop.
-It was, like -- It was Kristin.

24:33.080 --> 24:34.670
Which I know --

24:34.670 --> 24:36.670
Yeah, I know that's
her name, but it's not.

24:36.670 --> 24:38.420
Kristin -- the I-N from Kevin.

24:38.420 --> 24:40.750
Oh, my God!
There is a thing in my drink.

24:40.750 --> 24:42.210
It's a bug,
it's a bug thing.

24:42.210 --> 24:43.830
Don't -- Don't
look at it.

24:43.830 --> 24:45.420
It's a -- It's a scary --
It's too scary.

24:45.420 --> 24:47.000
Amy, will you please
help me come complain

24:47.000 --> 24:48.000
to the bartender
about the bug thing?

24:48.000 --> 24:50.420
-No.
-Amy, please.

24:57.460 --> 24:59.290
What are you doing?
Wingmanning.

24:59.290 --> 25:01.830
You got a bogey on your six,
and I'm shooting him down.

25:01.830 --> 25:03.790
Well, stop it, okay?
All of it.

25:03.790 --> 25:06.540
I didn't bring you here
to torpedo the date.

25:06.540 --> 25:07.880
I'm just doing you a solid.

25:07.880 --> 25:10.540
No! No solids
have been done, okay?

25:10.540 --> 25:14.750
Maybe Kristin and I
aren't meant to be.

25:14.750 --> 25:15.710
Fine.

25:15.710 --> 25:17.500
I'll leave it alone.

25:17.500 --> 25:20.330
Thank you.

25:20.330 --> 25:22.000
But you need to be
honest with yourself.

25:22.000 --> 25:24.500
Because if you're still
carrying something for Kristin,

25:24.500 --> 25:26.250
you need to sack up
and do something about it.

25:26.250 --> 25:27.880
Hmm.

25:27.880 --> 25:32.670
Pretty strong words from someone
who won't take her own advice.

25:32.670 --> 25:35.000
-Hey, Nate!
-What?

25:35.000 --> 25:36.290
-How's it going?
-Hey.

25:36.290 --> 25:37.620
-How do you feel about Nate?
-That's different.

25:37.620 --> 25:39.580
Mm?
Okay? Be discreet.

25:39.580 --> 25:41.120
Thank you.
But I don't want

25:41.120 --> 25:42.620
to ruin what we have.

25:42.620 --> 25:44.500
Well, I already did ruin
things with Kristin,

25:44.500 --> 25:47.750
so from one failure
to another, cheers.

25:47.750 --> 25:49.710
[ Glasses clink ]

25:49.710 --> 25:56.380
♪♪

25:56.380 --> 25:57.790
Ahh.

25:57.790 --> 25:59.330
[ Coughs ]
I win.

25:59.330 --> 26:01.960
I'm, like, disgusted and
impressed at the same time.

26:01.960 --> 26:03.790
It is pretty impressive,
isn't it?

26:03.790 --> 26:05.210
I can't do these
anymore.

26:05.210 --> 26:06.670
These are great.

26:06.670 --> 26:07.880
I'm starting
to come alive.

26:07.880 --> 26:08.790
I'm getting hot.
Is it hot?

26:08.790 --> 26:10.540
Can I have a beer?

26:10.540 --> 26:13.580
So, I sketched out a couple
ideas for the main backdrop.

26:13.580 --> 26:17.250
So it's supposed to be
Salem in the 1600s,

26:17.250 --> 26:20.620
but what if we set it in, like,
a messed-up sort of future?

26:20.620 --> 26:21.710
Like -- Like
"Blade Runner."

26:21.710 --> 26:23.580
Yes.
Cool!

26:23.580 --> 26:25.290
Everything else
will stay the same,

26:25.290 --> 26:27.380
but, see,
here's another idea.

26:27.380 --> 26:28.790
Started that one, too.

26:28.790 --> 26:31.580
Reese! Hey.

26:31.580 --> 26:33.750
Isn't that the girl who ate
my leftovers today?

26:33.750 --> 26:35.120
[ Laughter ]

26:35.120 --> 26:37.670
I have to get going.
I told my mom I'd be home early.

26:37.670 --> 26:45.380
♪♪

26:45.380 --> 26:52.960
♪♪

26:52.960 --> 26:54.330
Hey.

26:54.330 --> 26:55.880
You sure you don't
want to play?

26:55.880 --> 26:57.210
Oh, no. That's okay.

26:57.210 --> 26:59.290
Uh, seems like
it's going good.

26:59.290 --> 27:01.880
It's going --
It's going great.

27:01.880 --> 27:03.790
I -- I knew it would.

27:03.790 --> 27:06.540
You know, I can take it from
here if you want to split.

27:08.080 --> 27:09.960
Yeah. Uh, yeah.
I'm just gonna --

27:09.960 --> 27:12.460
I'll finish my beer
and take off.

27:12.460 --> 27:13.620
Have fun.

27:13.620 --> 27:15.500
[ Chuckles ]

27:17.830 --> 27:21.420
♪ She's my lady ♪

27:21.420 --> 27:22.880
♪♪

27:22.880 --> 27:26.120
He seems happy.

27:26.120 --> 27:27.170
Why wouldn't he be?

27:27.170 --> 27:29.170
Kristin is great.

27:29.170 --> 27:30.710
How'd you fix him?

27:30.710 --> 27:32.500
Because you need to do
the same thing to Tyler.

27:32.500 --> 27:35.710
I can't -- I can't stand
seeing him in this funk.

27:35.710 --> 27:39.000
Well, that's the thing --
I didn't really do anything

27:39.000 --> 27:42.620
but point Charlie
in a direction.

27:46.040 --> 27:48.540
He was ready to move on.
He just didn't know it.

27:48.540 --> 27:50.420
But how?

27:50.420 --> 27:52.670
How does one become
ready to move on?

27:52.670 --> 27:54.830
Uh...

27:55.960 --> 27:57.380
[ Laughs ]

28:00.960 --> 28:03.830
I...honestly don't know.

28:03.830 --> 28:06.830
[ Laughs ]

28:06.830 --> 28:09.040
You have to ask him.

28:09.540 --> 28:12.380
-Damn.
-Yep, that's four in a row.

28:12.380 --> 28:13.790
You owe me 20 bucks.

28:13.790 --> 28:15.880
Now, what's
the lesson you learn?

28:15.880 --> 28:18.040
Together: Never play pool
with an engineer.

28:18.040 --> 28:20.380
It's all about
geometry.

28:20.380 --> 28:23.750
Hey, uh, I think
I'm gonna get out of here.

28:23.750 --> 28:25.710
Um, can Nate
drive you home?

28:25.710 --> 28:26.880
Mm-hmm.

28:26.880 --> 28:30.460
You know, I'm actually
kind of done with pool.

28:30.460 --> 28:32.210
You want to get out of here
and do something stupid?

28:32.210 --> 28:33.580
I'm in.

28:33.580 --> 28:37.500
Uh...how stupid?

28:37.500 --> 28:39.920
Dealer's choice.

28:39.920 --> 28:41.830
Oh. So...

28:41.830 --> 28:43.880
incredibly stupid, then.

28:43.880 --> 28:48.710
♪♪

28:48.710 --> 28:51.710
Before college, I was --
I was positive that I wanted

28:51.710 --> 28:54.080
to be a doctor,
and then I had this just

28:54.080 --> 28:58.790
amazing history professor,
and, well, the rest is, um...

28:58.790 --> 29:02.210
Don't say "history."
Do not -- Do not say it.

29:02.210 --> 29:03.920
The rest is history.
Thanks. Yeah.

29:03.920 --> 29:05.670
[ Both laugh ]

29:05.670 --> 29:07.120
Another beer?

29:07.120 --> 29:09.040
Sure.
Yeah? Okay.

29:11.960 --> 29:14.830
Yvette: First date?

29:16.710 --> 29:18.120
[ Chuckles ]

29:18.120 --> 29:19.460
How can you tell?

29:19.460 --> 29:20.960
Um...

29:20.960 --> 29:22.500
You're laughing a little
too hard at her jokes.

29:22.500 --> 29:23.580
[ Both laugh ]

29:23.580 --> 29:25.000
And she was letting you
win at pool.

29:25.000 --> 29:26.420
[ Laughs ]

29:26.420 --> 29:27.880
It's been a while for me.

29:27.880 --> 29:30.710
Just got over a serious
relationship, so...

29:30.710 --> 29:33.880
And here you are,
finding love again.

29:33.880 --> 29:37.500
Well, I wouldn't
call it love just yet.

29:37.500 --> 29:39.960
We're still getting
to know each other.

29:39.960 --> 29:43.420
Yeah, um, you can't truly love
someone until you know them.

29:45.750 --> 29:49.920
So, it's a process.

29:49.920 --> 29:52.580
It's like love at first
sight isn't even real.

29:52.580 --> 29:54.330
Right.
Ah!

29:57.120 --> 30:00.210
Ac-- Actually, no.

30:00.210 --> 30:03.170
I take all that back.

30:03.170 --> 30:05.170
Love takes seconds.

30:07.000 --> 30:09.960
Erica -- uh, my ex.

30:09.960 --> 30:11.580
Erica and I fell in love

30:11.580 --> 30:15.540
the second we laid eyes
on one another.

30:15.540 --> 30:18.250
She took my breath away.

30:22.120 --> 30:24.620
Like a beach
on a summer day.

30:24.620 --> 30:27.040
Yeah.

30:27.040 --> 30:30.580
Exactly like that.

30:30.580 --> 30:33.670
So...

30:33.670 --> 30:37.960
So how -- how'd you
get over Erica?

30:37.960 --> 30:41.040
I...really don't know.

30:47.670 --> 30:49.120
That must've been weird,

30:49.120 --> 30:50.750
going on a double date
with your ex?

30:50.750 --> 30:52.790
And your sister?

30:52.790 --> 30:56.670
I can't stress enough --
it was a group hang.

30:56.670 --> 30:58.080
Okay.

30:58.080 --> 30:59.420
I'm set.

30:59.420 --> 31:01.210
So just give me the okay
when you guys are ready

31:01.210 --> 31:04.330
to witness some
bad-ass skate moves.

31:04.330 --> 31:06.120
Honestly, I think
he's wussing out.

31:06.120 --> 31:08.120
He just needs
to make a move.

31:08.120 --> 31:09.210
Me?

31:09.210 --> 31:11.210
Look at yourself.

31:11.210 --> 31:12.920
Look at the position
you're in right now.

31:12.920 --> 31:18.000
♪♪

31:18.000 --> 31:20.290
Okay. Fine.

31:20.290 --> 31:22.460
Nate, will you
go out on a --

31:22.460 --> 31:24.210
-Aah!
-Ohh!

31:24.210 --> 31:25.580
-God!
-Oh, my God!

31:25.580 --> 31:27.120
Oh, my God!
Are you okay?!

31:27.120 --> 31:28.380
-Oh, my God, no!
-Oh, Jesus.

31:28.380 --> 31:30.250
-Kevin, I'm gonna kill you!
-Sit up, sit up.

31:30.250 --> 31:31.540
-You said okay!
-I don't think

31:31.540 --> 31:33.080
I'm gonna make it.
-You said okay!

31:33.080 --> 31:34.080
-Look right.
-Did I chip a tooth?

31:34.080 --> 31:35.750
Yeah, yeah, you're fine.

31:35.750 --> 31:37.460
If she's talking, she's fine!
I can't move!

31:42.040 --> 31:43.580
Kevin: Ohh!
I can hear my rib parts.

31:43.580 --> 31:45.250
People don't have
rib parts.

31:45.250 --> 31:46.580
They have ribs.

31:46.580 --> 31:48.210
Chicken nuggets
have rib parts.

31:48.210 --> 31:50.040
Well, I have rib parts now,
and I can hear all of them.

31:50.040 --> 31:52.210
[ Grunts ]

31:52.210 --> 31:54.120
Amy, could you
get me some ice?

31:54.120 --> 31:55.210
Why me?

31:55.210 --> 31:57.080
You skated on my face.

31:57.080 --> 31:59.250
Because I'm already comfy,
and it was kind of your fault.

31:59.250 --> 32:00.880
You skated on my face!

32:00.880 --> 32:02.170
Oh, Amy,
I'm your brother!

32:02.170 --> 32:03.080
On my face!
Let's get some ice!

32:03.080 --> 32:04.420
Let's separate you two.

32:04.420 --> 32:05.790
Do you remember
skating on my face?!

32:05.790 --> 32:09.710
I'm asking for some ice,
as your brother!
Amy, Amy, please.

32:09.710 --> 32:10.880
[ Door closes ]

32:13.460 --> 32:23.500
♪♪

32:23.500 --> 32:24.790
Wha--

32:24.790 --> 32:32.290
♪♪

32:32.290 --> 32:34.170
Whoa!

32:34.170 --> 32:41.290
♪♪

32:41.290 --> 32:48.420
♪♪

32:48.420 --> 32:55.500
♪♪

32:55.500 --> 32:56.880
[ Laughs ]

32:56.880 --> 32:59.040
-Kevin!
-Oh.

32:59.040 --> 33:01.420
Yep. That's definitely
a concussion.

33:01.420 --> 33:02.920
No. I just --

33:02.920 --> 33:06.290
I was just doing stretches --
for the ribs.

33:06.290 --> 33:10.250
♪♪

33:10.250 --> 33:12.880
[ Shredder motor whirring ]

33:14.710 --> 33:17.380
[ Shredder motor whirring ]

33:18.250 --> 33:20.580
You're not even looking
at what you're shredding.

33:20.580 --> 33:23.290
Doesn't matter. I'm getting
rid of old baggage.

33:23.290 --> 33:24.620
It's a purge.

33:24.620 --> 33:27.210
Feels great.
Very freeing.

33:28.830 --> 33:31.500
Hey, you know that thing you do,
helping people and stuff?

33:31.500 --> 33:32.830
Mm-hmm.

33:32.830 --> 33:36.500
Does it ever, like,
backfire on you?

33:36.500 --> 33:38.000
Oh, yeah.

33:38.000 --> 33:40.290
Yeah, it, uh, backfires
big-time.

33:40.290 --> 33:43.000
But, um...

33:43.000 --> 33:46.080
Whoo-hoo. Lucky me --
I don't have a choice.

33:47.460 --> 33:49.080
Why not?

33:51.380 --> 33:55.460
Reese, people are always
going to need help,

33:55.460 --> 34:01.120
and I can't just look away
and pretend not to notice.

34:02.540 --> 34:04.460
Not anymore.

34:04.460 --> 34:08.460
I, um -- I have to do
the right thing, and...

34:12.670 --> 34:14.000
[ Chuckles ]

34:14.000 --> 34:15.750
...sometimes
the right thing sucks.

34:18.670 --> 34:20.420
Are you okay?

34:21.830 --> 34:25.000
Are you going through
a teen...crisis?

34:25.000 --> 34:27.250
Is there a mean girl
at school?

34:27.250 --> 34:30.710
Yeah, but I think
it's me.

34:30.710 --> 34:32.290
What -- What do you mean?

34:32.290 --> 34:35.170
Never mind.
I'll be down in a second.

34:39.000 --> 34:41.420
[ Shredder motor whirring ]

34:42.670 --> 34:45.080
[ Laughs ]

34:45.080 --> 34:51.960
♪♪

34:51.960 --> 34:54.960
[ Laughs ]
Will you look at that.

34:54.960 --> 34:57.380
How old
are you two there?

34:57.380 --> 34:59.540
18, senior year.
Oh!

34:59.540 --> 35:01.250
[ Laughing ]

35:01.250 --> 35:05.040
Oh, and by the way, I, uh...
got my vision last night.

35:05.040 --> 35:07.250
You did?
Mm-hmm.

35:07.250 --> 35:10.080
Looks like the next righteous
person is in someplace snowy,

35:10.080 --> 35:12.000
so I hope you
packed your parka.

35:12.000 --> 35:14.420
I -- I -- I don't get it.

35:14.420 --> 35:17.040
What -- What happened
to trigger the vision?

35:17.040 --> 35:21.790
Obviously, Kristin
and Charlie hit it off.

35:21.790 --> 35:24.420
Universe wants them together,
and because of me,

35:24.420 --> 35:26.620
they are, so yeehaw.

35:26.620 --> 35:28.500
[ Shredder motor whirring ]

35:30.710 --> 35:32.580
Knock it off, Universe.

35:32.580 --> 35:35.000
[ Shredder motor whirring ]

35:35.000 --> 35:37.830
It's not the Universe.

35:37.830 --> 35:38.790
This isn't funny.

35:38.790 --> 35:40.380
You can't shred that.

35:40.380 --> 35:42.170
I, for sure, can
if you let me.

35:42.170 --> 35:46.330
Tell me, what else was in that
pod from when you were 18?

35:46.330 --> 35:47.580
[ Scoffs ]

35:47.580 --> 35:49.120
Nothing, really.
I mean...

35:49.120 --> 35:52.790
So -- So you kept
that photo and only that photo

35:52.790 --> 35:56.290
since you left home?

35:56.290 --> 35:59.920
Yeah, I guess.
That seems dumb now.

35:59.920 --> 36:03.830
Human emotions are still
very confusing to me,

36:03.830 --> 36:08.920
but one thing
has become very clear.

36:08.920 --> 36:13.040
Love is an emotion that cannot
and will not be ignored.

36:13.040 --> 36:15.420
You can -- You can try
to stuff it down,

36:15.420 --> 36:18.040
you can -- you can
pretend it's over.

36:18.040 --> 36:22.500
But it's always there.

36:22.500 --> 36:25.750
Right now, you have
a chance at happiness.

36:25.750 --> 36:27.830
Why -- Why don't you take it?

36:27.830 --> 36:30.080
Because the Universe wants me
to get rid of everything,

36:30.080 --> 36:33.960
so, you know, that
obviously includes Kristin.

36:33.960 --> 36:37.880
What if the Universe
wants you to purge the things

36:37.880 --> 36:40.620
that aren't real,
to let go of the clutter,

36:40.620 --> 36:43.000
to reveal the one thing
that you've been holding on to

36:43.000 --> 36:45.120
since you left home?

36:45.120 --> 36:51.290
♪♪

36:51.290 --> 36:53.040
Reese: Okay. Ready.

36:55.380 --> 36:57.080
So am I.

37:02.500 --> 37:03.960
♪♪

37:03.960 --> 37:07.290
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:07.290 --> 37:16.080
♪♪

37:16.080 --> 37:25.120
♪♪

37:25.120 --> 37:26.540
[ Shoes squeal, body thuds ]

37:26.540 --> 37:28.250
-[ Gasps ]
-Watch the wet floor.

37:28.250 --> 37:30.420
Oh, my gosh.
Kevin, are you all right?

37:30.420 --> 37:32.290
Yeah. Um...

37:32.290 --> 37:34.750
Oh, it's just
the ribs again.

37:34.750 --> 37:36.750
Wow. Oh.
Oh.

37:36.750 --> 37:38.120
Just a second.
[ School bell rings ]

37:38.120 --> 37:40.880
[ Laughs ]
Um, so -- hi.

37:40.880 --> 37:42.120
Uh, about last night --

37:42.120 --> 37:44.170
Yeah, thanks a lot
for that.

37:44.170 --> 37:46.080
For what?

37:46.080 --> 37:48.620
Leaving me alone with an
emotionally unstable gentleman.

37:48.620 --> 37:50.120
Who, Charlie?

37:50.120 --> 37:52.750
It -- It was going great,
and then I went to order

37:52.750 --> 37:54.210
another round of beers,
I came back,

37:54.210 --> 37:56.670
and he was crying,
full tears.

37:56.670 --> 37:58.420
Wet napkins...

37:58.420 --> 38:00.670
I ended up driving him back
to his ex's place.

38:00.670 --> 38:03.250
They're in love again,
by the way.

38:03.250 --> 38:05.170
Uh --

38:05.170 --> 38:07.040
Oh! So he was meant
to get back with her,

38:07.040 --> 38:08.500
not to meet someone new.

38:08.500 --> 38:09.790
Huh?

38:09.790 --> 38:11.460
Huh? Oh! [ Stammers ]

38:11.460 --> 38:13.580
I think it's just
good news.

38:13.580 --> 38:16.830
It's great. I mean, that's
great news -- for Charlie.

38:16.830 --> 38:17.960
I mean, it's...
Yeah.

38:17.960 --> 38:20.380
...the best news.
I guess.

38:20.380 --> 38:21.620
Yeah, I mean --

38:21.620 --> 38:23.670
Well, so, I --

38:23.670 --> 38:25.290
'Cause I have also
sort of been --

38:25.290 --> 38:27.250
You know, I don't even
know why I went on a date --

38:27.250 --> 38:29.380
with anyone.

38:29.380 --> 38:30.580
Anyone?

38:30.580 --> 38:31.960
What do --

38:31.960 --> 38:33.460
Yeah.

38:33.460 --> 38:35.880
I don't know. I just --
I'm -- I'm still dealing

38:35.880 --> 38:38.540
with some stuff.

38:38.540 --> 38:40.040
Since my mom passed
and everything.

38:40.040 --> 38:41.960
Yeah.

38:41.960 --> 38:43.670
Yeah.

38:43.670 --> 38:46.670
Oh! Hey, I meant to tell you,
they actually opened

38:46.670 --> 38:48.040
a substitute-teacher
position.

38:48.040 --> 38:49.880
Oh.
And seeing as you were

38:49.880 --> 38:52.120
so good with my students
the other day,

38:52.120 --> 38:54.670
I submitted your name.

38:54.670 --> 38:56.080
Teaching kids?

38:56.080 --> 38:57.580
No, I don't know.
I don't know about that.

38:57.580 --> 38:59.500
Oh, come on.
It'll be fun.

38:59.500 --> 39:01.500
We'll get to
hang out more.

39:01.500 --> 39:05.040
Uh, yeah, that --
that could be good.

39:06.500 --> 39:09.290
Wait. Why are you here?

39:09.290 --> 39:11.620
Uh, Reese forgot
her book again today.

39:11.620 --> 39:13.790
Oh.

39:13.790 --> 39:15.750
Which I forgot, too.

39:15.750 --> 39:17.620
[ Laughs ] Okay.

39:17.620 --> 39:20.250
Well, I guess I'll, um --
I'll just see you around.

39:20.250 --> 39:21.330
Yeah.

39:21.330 --> 39:23.580
Maybe as the new
substitute teacher.

39:23.580 --> 39:26.290
Oh.
'Cause anything's
possible, Kevin.

39:26.290 --> 39:27.330
Bye.

39:27.330 --> 39:28.960
Bye.

39:28.960 --> 39:38.960
♪♪

39:38.960 --> 39:43.250
♪♪

39:45.670 --> 39:47.620
-Who is it?
-It's me.

39:47.620 --> 39:49.830
I, uh, brought you
the extra-strength stuff

39:49.830 --> 39:50.830
from the first-aid locker.

39:50.830 --> 39:52.620
Amy: Oh, great.

39:52.620 --> 39:53.790
Uh, you could just --

39:53.790 --> 39:54.920
Uh, you could
leave it out there.

39:54.920 --> 39:55.750
Thank you.

39:55.750 --> 39:56.960
Can I come in?

39:56.960 --> 39:59.080
No.
Really?

39:59.080 --> 40:00.710
Yeah, I don't
look so good.

40:02.460 --> 40:03.830
Yes.

40:06.710 --> 40:08.120
"Yes" what?

40:08.120 --> 40:10.620
To your question, yes.

40:10.620 --> 40:15.080
I'd be very happy to go out
on a date with you.

40:15.080 --> 40:16.500
No take-backs?

40:16.500 --> 40:18.460
Pinky swear.

40:22.500 --> 40:24.620
Oh.

40:24.620 --> 40:27.540
Is it that bad?

40:27.540 --> 40:30.540
I'm-a see you in two weeks
when you're all healed up.

40:30.540 --> 40:31.580
You are a jerk!

40:31.580 --> 40:33.040
I hate you!

40:35.120 --> 40:39.710
[ Indistinct chatter ]

40:40.540 --> 40:42.670
Hey.

40:42.670 --> 40:44.620
Why don't you
come sit with us?

40:44.620 --> 40:47.790
Uh, no, it's -- it's cool
if you're embarrassed.

40:51.330 --> 40:54.960
They gave me
way too much spaghetti.

40:54.960 --> 40:57.380
There's no way
I'm gonna finish it all.

40:57.380 --> 40:59.040
Yeah?

40:59.040 --> 41:02.880
And Rory said you can have
the crust to his sandwich.

41:02.880 --> 41:04.750
-Hey.
-[ Laughs ]

41:04.750 --> 41:06.000
Yeah, okay.

41:06.000 --> 41:08.040
[ Laughs ]

41:09.710 --> 41:12.710
So, you're finally
getting a job.

41:12.710 --> 41:17.750
Kristin wants me around
in her vicinity, and, um...

41:17.750 --> 41:21.580
that means that when she's ready
to date, I will be there.

41:21.580 --> 41:23.000
Like a stalker.

41:23.000 --> 41:26.000
Like a friend...ly
stalker.

41:26.000 --> 41:28.330
[ Both laugh ]

41:28.330 --> 41:32.830
You do realize that you will
have to teach children.

41:32.830 --> 41:34.710
I'm a sub.
That's what movies are for.

41:34.710 --> 41:36.120
[ Scoffs ]

41:36.120 --> 41:37.380
But still, sorry
you didn't get a chance

41:37.380 --> 41:39.580
to tell her how you feel.

41:39.580 --> 41:41.670
